From Alan Ezekiel Subject Re The Dayton Gun Buy Back Re Boston Gun Buy Back Larry Cipriani writes According to WNCI FM radio this morning Dayton Ohio is operating a gun buy back They are giving for every functional gun turned They ran out of money in one day and are now passing out vouchers of some They are looking for more funds to keep Another media event brought to you by Is there something similar pro gun people can do For example pay to anyone who lawfully protects their life with a firearm Sounds a bit tacky but hey whatever As David Veal points out this sort of promotion would be used against gun owners by the mass However here is my proposal offer gun safety classes in your area free as a community Such a class would normally cost or so offering it free is a good Our Gun Club has organized several of these we just finished teaching another one last night in fact and they have been very well We get a lot of people who are novices interested in We even get a few who are anti gun but feel they should know something about gun safety since members of their family keep guns at Teaching such a course gives us many desirable benefits We have the chance to teach gun safety rules this increases firearm awareness and may help to reduce gun accident A gun safety class is Politically Correct and likely to be viewed positively by the public and the Most of the students are 'normal people' not gun enthusiasts and this kind of class gives us the chance to give them a gentle introduction to Some of the students are enthusiastic and will purchase a gun and become more involved in shooting or personal It improves the public perception of our club and gun owners in Our students see that we are all reasonable non aggressive soft spoken people which helps to mitigate the standard image of a hardcore gun Even anti gun students sometimes tell us they have something new to think about with regards to personal gun Sharing our experience with others is a lot of Our course is the standard NRA certified Home Firearm Safety class and our students pay only for We also teach the NRA's Personal Protection class although the cost is higher for that one since we have to purchase range I think firearms safety classes are an excellent response to gun buy Alane NOBODY shares my opinions I am a jelly doughnut especially not my employer President John F Kennedy